<h1>Problem 1174 - 2013 IMOSL, G3, G</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 8</h2>
<p>In a triangle \(ABC\), let \(D\) and \(E\) be the feet of the angle bisectors of angles \(A\) and \(B\), respectively. A rhombus is inscribed into the quadrilateral \(AEDB\) (all vertices of the rhombus lie on different sides of \(AEDB\)). Let \(\varphi\) be the non-obtuse angle of the rhombus. Prove that \(\varphi \le \max \{  \angle BAC, \angle ABC  \}\).</p>
